Thailand Stocks: Asia Plus, Kim Eng, PTT Exploration, Thai Oil

-- B y   A n u c h i t   N g u y e n
-- 
2011-04-04T03:32:11Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-04/lpn-development-ptt-thai-oil-thailand-equity-preview.html
Shares of the following companies
had unusual moves in  Thailand  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 10:24 a.m. in Bangkok.  The SET Index rose 11.93, or 1.1 percent, to 1,076.28,
headed for the highest close since October 1996.  Energy companies:  PTT Pcl (PTT)  , Thailand’s biggest
energy company, climbed 2 percent to 364 baht, poised for the
highest close since May 2008.  PTT Exploration & Production Pcl (PTTEP) 
, the nation’s only publicly traded oil explorer,
jumped 4.3 percent to 192.5 baht, bound for the highest close
since June 2008.  Banpu Pcl (BANPU)  , the biggest coal
producer, advanced 1 percent to 780 baht.  Crude oil climbed for a third day in  New York , trading at a
30-month high, as signs of economic recovery in the U.S. boosted
speculation fuel demand will rise in the world’s largest crude
user.  Stock brokerages: Kim Eng Securities (Thailand) Pcl, the
country’s largest stock brokerage, rose 2.1 percent to 14.7
baht.  Asia Plus Securities Pcl (ASP)   added 2 percent to 3.04
baht.  Bualuang Securities Pcl (BLS)   gained 2.1 percent to
24.3 baht.  Share trading turnover surged to 48.3 billion baht ($1.6
billion) on April 1, the highest since Dec. 8, according to
Stock Exchange of Thailand data.  Thai Oil Pcl (TOP)  , the largest Thai oil refiner by
market value, increased 2.1 percent to 86.75 baht, headed for
the highest close since December 2007. The company expects
first-half sales and profit to rise compared with the same
period last year because of wider refinery margins and higher
product prices, Chief Executive Officer Surong Bulakul said. The
company may increase its forecast for operating profit this
year, from a current target of about 8 billion baht, he said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Anuchit Nguyen in Bangkok at 
